gnm:Cells.gnm:Cell: Claims Counts
Response
Report Definition
Volume of Open Claims
(Number)
Total number of open claim as at report date
Volume of Closed Claims
(Number)
Total number of closed claims from start of reporting period to report date
Volume of Reopened Claims
(Number)
Total number of clams re-opened from start of reporting period to report date
Volume of New Claims
(Number)
Total number of new claims created from start of reporting period to report date
Value of open claims
(As At Report Date)
Total value of all open claims as at report date
% of work referred to London?
(Percentage)
Total volume of work referred to London divided by total volume of claims processed from start of reporting peroid to report date
Volume of files held open for recovery/subrogation
(Number)
Total number of open claims with recovery/subrogation reserve as at report date
Performance
% Open claims referred to UW's outside of Market 5 day SLA
(Percentage)
Total number of claims referred to U/W over 5 days from notification from start of reporting period divided by total number of open claims as at report date
Volume of Claims not acknowledged within Market 48 hours SLA
(Number)

Number of claims from start of reporting period that have an acknowledgement date that is greater than 48 hours from notification date or has a blank acknowledgement date and report date is greater than 48 hours from notification date
Volume of overdue diary items in the last reporting period?
(Number)
Total number of overdue diary items from start of reporting period to report date
% of Open Claims peer reviewed
(Percentage)
Number of claims from start of reporting period that have been reviewed divided by the total number of open claims as at report date
What is the average days taken from 1st notification to 1st indemnity payment
(As At Report Date)

Sum of total number of days between the 1st notification date and 1st indemnity payment date on all claims that had a 1st notification and indemnity payment in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of claims with a 1st notification and indemnity payment in this reporting period
What is the average days taken from 1st notification to close
(As At Report Date)

Sum of total number of days between the 1st notification date and closed date on all claims that had a 1st notification and are now closed date in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of claims with a 1st notification and closed in this reporting period
Average number of days to establish initial reserve from notice of claim
(As At Report Date)

Sum of total number of days between the 1st notification date and first entered reserve date on all claims that had a 1st notification and have a reserve in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of claims with a 1st notification and reserve in this reporting period
Variance of final to initial reserve (as %)
(As At Report Date)
Calculate the first reserve value minus final reserve value divided by first reserve value x 100 to give you the percentage
Volume of nil reserve claims older than 6 months (as percentage)
(Percentage)

Number of claims from start of reporting period that have a 1st notification date that is greater than 6 months as at report date and a nil reserve divided by the total number of open claims as at report date
Communication
Response time for acknowledging new claims
(Number)

Sum of total number of days between the 1st notification received date and acknowledgement date on all claims that had a 1st notification and have an acknowldegement date in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of claims with a 1st notification and acknowledgement date in this reporting period
Response time for first party correspondence
(Number)

Sum of total number of days between the received date of first party correspondence and response date on all claims that had first party correspondence received and have a response date in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of claims with first party correspondence and a response date in this reporting period
Time taken to issue payment (from date of agreement)
(Number)

Sum of total number of days between the agreement date and payment date on all claims that have an agreement date and payment date in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of claims with an agreement date and payment date in this reporting period
3rd Party Adjuster Usage
Total volume of field adjuster instructions made in the reporting period?
(Number)
Total number of field adjuster instructions from start of reporting period to report date
Volume of field adjuster instructions issued to non-affiliated companies?
(Number)
Total number of field adjuster instructions issued to non-affiliated companies from start of reporting period to report date
Volume of initial reports that have not been issued within 30 days SLA (either to the Syndicate or by 3rd party expert to TPA)
(Number)

Number of initial reports from start of reporting period that have an issued date that is equal to or greater than 30 days from instruction date or has a blank issued date and report date is equal to or greater than 30 days from instruction date
Claim Complaints
Volume of Claim Complaints received
(Number)
Total number of claim complaints from start of reporting period to report date
Volume of Claims Examiners
How many full time Claims Examiners do you have?
(Number)
Total number of full time Claims Examiners as at report date
What is the average case load count per Claim examiner on all contracts?
(Number)
Sum of total number of cases in the reporting period as at report date. Divide this total by total number of Claims Examiners in this reporting period
How many claims Examiners have left in the past reporting period?
(Number)
Total number of leavers from start of reporting period to report date
